Westville Boys’ High School had a good sporting day at the St Charles College in Pietermaritzburg on Saturday 30, April. The Westville side battled it out with the host, St Charles in rugby and hockey. Hockey boys played 12 matches, won eight, and lost just two. The rugby team played five games and secured a clean win of all five games. Westville Boys’ High School’s Thomas Jackson said: “Thank you to St Charles College for the warm welcome and hosting us on Saturday.”